      <div style="padding:24px 28px">
        <p><strong>Islamic Major Sign:</strong> One of the ten Major Signs of the Hour is the <em>sun rising from the west</em> (Sahih Muslim 2941, Sahih Bukhari 4635). When this occurs, repentance is no longer accepted. This is considered one of the most dramatic and irreversible signs.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Biblical parallel — Matthew 24:29:</strong> "Immediately after the tribulation of those days the sun will be darkened, and the moon will not give its light; the stars will fall from the sky, and the heavenly bodies will be shaken."</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Joel 2:31</strong> (quoted in Acts 2:20): "The sun will be turned to darkness and the moon to blood before the coming of the great and glorious day of the Lord."</p>
        <p style="margin-top:12px"><strong>Revelation 6:12:</strong> Sixth seal — "the sun turned black like sackcloth made of goat hair, the whole moon turned blood red."</p>
        <div class="callout" style="margin-top:16px">
          <strong>The Observation:</strong> Both traditions describe dramatic, unprecedented solar events immediately before the final judgment. The Islamic sign (rising from west) and Biblical signs (darkened, turned blood) may describe the same astronomical event from different observational frameworks — or they may describe sequential events in the same prophetic sequence. Either way, cosmic solar disruption appears in BOTH traditions as a Major Sign of the Hour/End.
        </div>
